  "title": "A Strain of Colletotrichum gloeosporioides Causing Anthracnose on Yellow Sorghum",
  "abstract": "Anthracnose, Colletotrichum sublineolum (Henn., Kabat et. Bub.) (=C. graminicola(Ces.) Wils.), can cause considerable yield losses in sorghum (Harris and Fisher 1974, Mishra and Siradhana 1979, Thakur 1995). The authors observed a new pathogen causing anthracnose in yellow sorghum in India.",
